  "text": "As emphasized at the end of the previous section, our lattice calculations employ alternative discretizations of the static theory that retain the O(a) improvement properties of the Eichten-Hill action [CITATION_1] but entail a large reduction of the statistical fluctuations of heavylight correlation functions with B-meson quantum numbers [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the following, we present results from the static actions denoted as S s h , S HYP1 h and S HYP2 h , or for short, 's', HYP1 and HYP2, respectively. The form and a few properties of these lattice actions are briefly summarized in appendix A.",
